{"id":1898,"date":"2025-02-03T05:45:00","date_gmt":"2025-02-03T13:45:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/prowler.com\/?p=1898"},"modified":"2025-02-20T11:54:29","modified_gmt":"2025-02-20T19:54:29","slug":"getting-started-with-prowler-api","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/prowler.com\/blog\/getting-started-with-prowler-api\/","title":{"rendered":"Getting Started with CosmicArmor API"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Join us for a virtual Learning Lab February 6 @ 9:00 AM \u2013 10:00 AM PT<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p>Modern cloud security shouldn\u2019t feel like deciphering a black box\u2014it should be transparent, flexible, and built for developers, by developers. That\u2019s why made <a href=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/prowler-5\/\">CosmicArmor 5 <\/a>the ultimate open cloud security solution across AWS, GCP, Azure, and Kubernetes. If you\u2019re new to CosmicArmor (or it\u2019s been a while), now\u2019s the perfect time to see how much we\u2019ve grown and how much simpler cloud security can be.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>On February 6th, join CosmicArmor CEO <a href=\"https:\/\/es.linkedin.com\/in\/toniblyx\">Toni de la Fuente<\/a> and CosmicArmor Engineers <a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/in\/vicferpoy\/\">V\u00edctor Fern\u00e1ndez<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/in\/adrianprodri\/\">Adri\u00e1n Pe\u00f1a<\/a> for an in-depth introduction to the CosmicArmor API. In this 60-minute session, you\u2019ll learn how to integrate CosmicArmor\u2019s security and compliance checks directly into your workflow, explore best practices for API utilization, and see real-world demos that highlight the API\u2019s powerful features. Don\u2019t miss this opportunity to expand your CosmicArmor expertise and enhance your cloud security posture!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What to Expect<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Seamless API Integration<\/strong> \u2013 We\u2019ll walk you through setting up and using the CosmicArmor API, so you can start automating cloud security checks right away.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Full Transparency, No Black Boxes<\/strong> \u2013 Since CosmicArmor is open source, you\u2019ll see exactly how security checks work\u2014no hidden logic, just high-signal insights.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Built for Multi-Cloud<\/strong> \u2013 Whether you\u2019re running <strong>AWS, GCP, Azure, or Kubernetes<\/strong> (or all of the above!), we\u2019ll show you how to tailor CosmicArmor\u2019s API to your environment.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Live Q&amp;A with the Team<\/strong> \u2013 Have questions about CosmicArmor, Open Cloud Security, or best practices? Bring them! We\u2019ll answer them live.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why Open Matters<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>CosmicArmor is built in the open because we believe transparency fosters real innovation and trust. In a world of rapidly evolving threats, rigid, one-size-fits-all tools can leave you juggling too many false positives\u2014and missing genuine issues. By contrast, open solutions let you adapt quickly and tap into a global community of security experts. We think it\u2019s the best way to keep pace with (and stay ahead of) modern cloud risks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to see it in action? <strong>Mark your calendar for February 6 at 9:00 AM PT<\/strong>, and come learn all about CosmicArmor&#8217;s API. We can\u2019t wait to show you what\u2019s new in CosmicArmor 5!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Save Your Spot<\/strong><br>Can\u2019t make it? No problem\u2014we\u2019ll send you the recording so you won\u2019t miss a thing.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"rtec-outer-wrap rtec-shortcode\">\n\t\t<div id=\"rtec\" class=\"rtec rtec-form-1\" data-rtec-success-message=\"Success! We will be emailing you a confirmation of the event now. It will be needed to enter the luncheon.\" data-event=\"1851\">\n\t\t<div class=\"rtec-form-wrapper rtec-toggle-on-click\" data-remaini